\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We have shown how to realize a Bell test in continuous variables position
 and momentum using specifically chosen and physically realizable states.
 In addition it has been demonstrated that the exact pauli commutation relations
 aren't necessary to capture the essence of non-locality; infact by relaxing
 the similarity, the set of states that show a violation is made considerably
 larger.
